<h3 id="the-project">The Project</h3>
<p>In January 2016, the UCLA Mechanical Engineering Senior Class was split into groups of five, and assigned a task:</p>

<h5 id="create-a-robot-that"><strong>Create a robot that</strong></h5>
<ol>
  <li>Is completely autonomous</li>
  <li>Can navigate a twisty and hilly course</li>
  <li>Can launch a golf ball precisely 4 feet +/- 10% from the end of course</li>
  <li>Can traverse the course back to the starting point</li>
  <li>Uses active steering</li>
  <li>Can do this in under 2.5 minutes</li>
  <li>Fits within an 11‚Äù x 11‚Äù x 11‚Äù volume</li>
  <li>Costs less than $375</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/iSYXKaR.png" style="width:100%; max-width: 600px;" /></p>

<p class="mycaption"><strong>The Course</strong></p>

<hr />

<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/MXwZxM3.png" style="width:100%; max-width: 600px;" /></p>

<p class="mycaption"><strong>The Best Team Ever</strong></p>

<hr />

<h3 id="design">Design</h3>
<p>We had to make some critical design decisions early that would affect our process thereafter.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Number of wheels
    <ul>
      <li>We went with three wheels.  The two rears can be powered through a single axle.  The front steering wheel can be actively steered with a servo.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Sensor placement
    <ul>
      <li>Left and Right sensors located near the centerline, forward and rear sensors angled downward.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Launch mechanism
    <ul>
      <li>A <em>wicked</em> winch that loads a spring and quick releases a piston that pushes the ball out and up.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Drivetrain
    <ul>
      <li>Belt-driven solid rear axle.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="computer-aided-design">Computer Aided Design</h3>

<p>We had to have an accurate CAD by the end of 162D, which we would then build during 162E.</p>

